### Identity Cosmos replication — manual test & trigger
### Host: StockPlusPlus.Functions  (local port comes from Properties/launchSettings.json → --port 7143)
### Run the Functions host first:  func start   (or F5 / dotnet run)

@host = http://localhost:7143

# Deployed only — locally both endpoints are open (no key needed).
# The HTTP endpoint is AuthorizationLevel.Function; the /admin endpoint needs the host master key.
# Uncomment and fill in for a deployed host, then append the key as shown per request.
# @functionKey = <replicate-all function key>
# @masterKey   = <host master/_master key>


###############################################################################
# 1) ON-DEMAND FULL RE-SYNC  (updateAll: true — re-syncs EVERY identity row)
#    ✅ Works in Development. This is the main way to test replication locally.
#    Requires CosmosDb:Enabled=true + a reachable Cosmos (emulator on :8081).
#    Returns { "replicated": true }  — or { "replicated": false, "reason": … }
#    when Cosmos is disabled/unconfigured.
###############################################################################

### Replicate ALL identity entities now (Services, Departments, Brands, Regions,
### Countries, Cities, CompanyBranches, Companies, Teams, Users + the M:N joins)
POST {{host}}/api/replicate-all
# Deployed: add ?code={{functionKey}}  — or the header:  x-functions-key: {{functionKey}}


###############################################################################
# 2) TRIGGER AN INDIVIDUAL HOURLY TIMER  (via the Functions admin endpoint)
#    ⚠ The timers are DISABLED in local dev via AzureWebJobs.<name>.Disabled in
#      local.settings.json, so the host does NOT load them locally and the admin
#      calls below return 404. To exercise ONE locally: set its
#      AzureWebJobs.<name>.Disabled to "false" in local.settings.json, restart the
#      host, then send its request. On a deployed (non-dev) host they run on the
#      hourly schedule and can be triggered on demand here with the master key.
#      Each timer does a dirty-only incremental sync (updateAll: false).
#    Deployed: add the header  x-functions-key: {{masterKey}}
###############################################################################

### Services
POST {{host}}/admin/functions/ReplicateServicesTimer
Content-Type: application/json

{ "input": "" }

### CompanyBranch ↔ Service joins  (branch sub-items)
POST {{host}}/admin/functions/ReplicateCompanyBranchServicesTimer
Content-Type: application/json

{ "input": "" }

### CompanyBranch ↔ Department joins  (branch sub-items)
POST {{host}}/admin/functions/ReplicateCompanyBranchDepartmentsTimer
Content-Type: application/json

{ "input": "" }

